usiness process outsourcing companies]]\n[[Category:Outsourcing in India]]\n[[Category:Computer companies of India]]\n[[Category:Information technology companies of Bhubaneswar]]\n[[Category:Indian brands]]\n[[Category:1945 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Karnataka]]\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|Wipro Enterprises}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2014}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2014}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name =  Wipro Limited\n| logo = Wipro Logo 1.png\n| logo_size = 100px\n| image = S3 and S4 Building SJP2 Wipro Sarjapur office Photo 182805.jpg\n| image_size = 260px\n| image_caption = Wipro headquarters in Sarjapur Rd, [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]], [[India]]\n| type = [[Public company|Public]]\n| traded_as = {{Unbulleted list|{{BSE|507685}}|{{NSE|WIPRO}}|{{NYSE|WIT}}|[[BSE SENSEX|BSE SENSEX Constituent]]|[[S&P CNX Nifty|CNX Nifty Constituent]]}}\n| founder = Sudipto Halder\n| area_served = Worldwide\n| key_people = {{Unbulleted list|[[Rishad Premji]] {{Small|(Chairman)}}|[[Abidali Neemuchwala]] {{Small|(CEO)}}}}\n| industry = [[Conglomerate (company)|Conglomerate]]\n| products = {{Flatlist|\n* [[Personal care]]\n* [[Health care]]\n* [[Lighting]]\n* [[Furniture]]\n}}\n| services = {{Flatlist|\n* [[Digital strategy]]\n* [[IT service management|IT services]]\n* [[Consulting]] \n* [[Outsourcing]]\n* [[Managed services]] \n}}\n| revenue = {{increase}} {{USD|8.47 billion|link=yes}} (2019)<ref name=6-K>{{cite web|url=http://www.wipro.com/investors/financial-information/quarterly-results/|title=Wipro Financial Statements 2019|publisher=Wipro Ltd|access-date=20 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160408042010/http://www.wipro.com/investors/financial-information/quarterly-results/|archive-date=8 April 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| operating_income = {{increase}} {{USD|1.66 billion}} (2019)<ref name=6-K/>\n| net_income = {{increase}} {{USD|1.3 billion}} (2019)<ref name=6-K/>\n| assets = {{increase}} {{USD|12.04 billion}} (2019)<ref name=6-K/>\n| equity = {{increase}} {{USD|8.25 billion}} (2019)<ref name=6-K/>\n| owner = Azim Premji (73.85%)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=a48f1bf0-8180-11e9-8842-a57b17f9d5b9&url=L2JpbGxpb25haXJlcy9wcm9maWxlcy9hemltLWgtcHJlbWppLw==|title=Bloomberg - Are you a robot?|website=www.bloomberg.com|accessdate=28 May 2019}}</ref>\n| num_employees =  171,425 (2019)<ref name=6-K/>\n| foundation = {{Start date and age|29 December 1945}}\n| location =  \n| hq_location_city = [[Bangalore]]\n| hq_location_country = [[India]]\n| homepage = {{URL|http://www.wipro.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Wipro''' (formerly, Western India Palm Refined Oil Limited, legally ''' Wipro Limited''') is an Indian [[multinational corporation]] that provides [[information technology]], consulting and business process services. It is headquartered in [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]], [[India]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wipro.com/en-IN/about-us/|title=About Wipro|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181016165304/https://www.wipro.com/en-IN/about-us/|archive-date=16 October 2018|url-status=live|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, Wipro separated its non-IT businesses and formed the privately owned [[Wipro Enterprises]].<ref name=\"thehindubusinessline\"/>\n{{TOC limit}}\n\n==History==\n===Early years===\nThe company was incorporated on 29 December 1945 in [[Amalner]], [[Maharashtra]] by Mohamed Premji as \"Western India Palm Refined Oil Limited\", later abbreviated to \"Wipro\". It was initially set up as a manufacturer of vegetable and [[cooking oil#Refinement|refined oils]] in [[Amalner]], Maharashtra, British India, under the [[trade name]]<nowiki/>s of Kisan, Sunflower, and Camel.<ref name=NPHistory/><ref name=\"moneycontrol-wipro-history\"/><ref name=\"companyhistory\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wipro.com/about-Wipro/|title=\"About Wipro\"|website=wipro.com|accessdate=22 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170922040551/http://www.wipro.com/about-Wipro/|archive-date=22 September 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 1966, after Mohamed Premji's death, his son [[Azim Premji]] took over Wipro as its [[chairman]] at the age of 21.<ref name=\"Billionaire Profile: Azim Premji\"/><ref name=\"Financial Express\"/>\n\nDuring the 1970s and 1980s, the company shifted its focus to new opportunities in the IT and computing industry, which was at a nascent stage in India at the time. On 7 June 1977, the name of the company changed from Western India Vegetable Products Limited, to Wipro Products Limited.<ref name=\"moneycontrol-wipro-history\"/> In 1982, the name was changed again, from Wipro Products Limited to Wipro Limited.<ref name=\"Company profile for Wipro\" /> Wipro continued to expand in the consumer products domain with the launch of \"Ralak\" a [[Tulsi]] based family soap and \"Wipro Jasmine\", a toilet soap.\n\n===1986\u20131992===\nIn 1988, Wipro added mobile hydraulic cylinders and heavy-duty industrial cylinders to its line of products.<ref name=\"moneycontrol-wipro-history\"/> A joint venture company with the United States' [[General Electric]] in the name of Wipro GE Medical Systems Pvt. Ltd. was set up in 1989 for the manufacture, sales, and service of diagnostic and imaging products.<ref name=\"economictimes-wipro-history\"/> In 1991, tipping systems and Eaton hydraulic products were launched. The Wipro Fluid Power division, in 1992, developed the capability to offer standard hydraulic cylinders for construction equipment and truck tipping systems. The \"Santoor\" talcum powder and \"Wipro Baby Soft\" range of baby toiletries were launched in 1990.<ref name=\"economictimes-wipro-history\"/>\n\n===1994\u20132000===\nIn 1995, Wipro set up an overseas design centre, Odyssey 21, for the projects of overseas clients. Wipro Infotech and Wipro Systems were amalgamated with Wipro in April that year.<ref name=\"economictimes-wipro-history\"/> Five of Wipro's manufacturing and development facilities secured the ISO 9001 certification during 1994\u201395.\n\nIn 1999, Wipro acquired Wipro Acer.<ref name=\"Corporate Round-up\" /> Wipro released new products such as the Wipro SuperGenius personal computers (PCs). In 1999, the product was the one Indian PC range to obtain US-based National Software Testing Laboratory ([[National Software Testing Laboratories|NSTL]]) certification for the Year 2000 ([[Y2K]]) compliance in hardware for all models.<ref name=\"In brief\" />\n\nWipro Limited joined with [[KPN]] (Royal Dutch telecom) to form a [[joint venture]] company \"Wipro Net Limited\" to provide internet services in India.<ref name=\"Financial Express\"/> In 2000 Wipro launched Wipro OSS Smart and Wipro WAP Smart.<ref name=\"Wipro releases WAP solutions\"/> In the same year, Wipro was listed on the [[New York Stock Exchange]].<ref name=\"Wipro lists on NYSE with marginal premium\"/>\n\n===2001\u20132010===\nIn February 2002, Wipro became the first [[software]] technology and services company in India to be [[ISO 14001]] certified.<ref name=\"Wipro Tech gets ISO 14001\"/> Wipro Consumer Care and Lighting Group entered the market of [[compact fluorescent lamp]]<nowiki/>s, with the launch of a range of CFL, under the brand name of Wipro Smartlite.<ref name=\"Wipro lighting launches new range\"/> As the company grew, a study revealed that Wipro was the fastest wealth creator for 5 years (1997\u20132002).<ref name=\"Wipro Is Fastest Wealth Creator For 5 Years: Study\"/><ref name=\"Wipro is biggest wealth creator during 1998-2003: Study\"/> It set up a wholly owned subsidiary company (Wipro Consumer Care Limited) to manufacture consumer care and lighting products.<ref name=\"Wipro to set up consumer care unit in Himachal\"/> In 2004 Wipro joined the billion dollar club.<ref name=\"Wipro joins billion dollar club, announces 2:1 bonus shares\"/> It also partnered with [[Intel]] for i-shiksha.<ref name=\"Wipro and Intel launch 'I-Shiksha' solution\"/><ref name=\"Wipro, Intel Join Forces to Launch i-shiksha\"/> In 2006, Wipro acquired cMango Inc., a US-based technology infrastructure consulting firm,<ref name=\"thehindubusinessline2006\"/><ref name=\"Wipro bags US consulting co cMango\"/> and a Europe-based retail provider.<ref name=\"India's Wipro acquires Enabler\"/> In 2007, Wipro signed a deal with Lockheed Martin.<ref name=\"Lockheed Martin, Wipro To Light Ambar Jyoti in India\"/><ref name=\"Wipro-Lockheed-Martin\"/> It also agreed to acquire Oki Techno Centre Singapore Pte Ltd (OTCS)<ref name=\"Wipro-Lockheed-Martin\"/><ref name=\"Wipro to Acquire Oki's Wireless Chip Design Arm\"/> and signed an R&D partnership contract with Nokia Siemens Networks in Germany.<ref name=\"Wipro to manage R&D for Nokia Siemens\"/><ref name=\"Wipro to buy Nokia Siemens R&D unit in Berlin\"/>\n\nIn 2008, Wipro's entered the clean energy business with Wipro Eco Energy.<ref name=\"The Inside Story of Azim Premji's Next Billion Dollar Plan\"/><ref name=\"Stable, yet supple\"/>\n\n===2011-2018===\nIn April 2011, Wipro signed an agreement with [[Science Applications International Corporation]] (SAIC) for the acquisition of their global oil and gas information technology practice.<ref name=\"indiatimes\"/><ref name=\"reuters\"/> In 2012, Wipro employed more than 70,000 temporary workers in the United States.<ref name=\"Top 10 Employers\"/>\n\nIn 2012, Wipro acquired Australian Trade Promotions Management firm Promax Applications Group (PAG) for $35 million.<ref name=\"Wipro to acquire Australia's Promax Applications Group for Rs 192 crore\"/><ref name=\"business-standard\"/> Also, in that year, Wipro Ltd. demerged its consumer care, lighting, furniture, infrastructure engineering (hydraulics and water and medical diagnostic business) into a separate company to be named 'Wipro Enterprises Ltd'.<ref name=\"Wipro hives off non-IT business into separate company\"/><ref name=\"Wipro's Scheme of Arrangement for Demerger Effective from March 31, 2013\"/><ref name=\"Wipro demerger scheme comes into effect\"/> Prior to demerger, these companies together contributed about 10% of the revenues of  Wipro Limited.<ref name=\"Wipro to demerge non-IT businesses\"/><ref name=\"Azim Premji says son Rishad will never be CEO of Wipro\"/>\n\nIn 2014, Wipro signed a 10-year $1.2 billion contract with [[ATCO]], a Canadian Energy and Utilities corporation based in [[Calgary, Alberta]]. This was the largest deal in Wipro's history.<ref name = \"Canada Progress\"/> In October 2016, Wipro announced that it was buying [[Appirio]], an [[Indianapolis]]-based cloud services company for $500 million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wipro.com/newsroom/press-releases/Wipro-to-acquire-Appirio-A-global-cloud-services-company/|title=Wipro to acquire Appirio, A Global Cloud Services Company|website=www.wipro.com|access-date=2016-12-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161226145503/http://www.wipro.com/newsroom/press-releases/Wipro-to-acquire-Appirio-A-global-cloud-services-company/|archive-date=26 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2016/10/20/indias-wipro-buys-cloud-services-consultancy-appirio-for-500m/|title=India\u2019s Wipro buys cloud consultancy and work marketplace Appirio for $500M|last=Lunden|first=Ingrid|website=TechCrunch|access-date=2016-12-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180110174712/https://techcrunch.com/2016/10/20/indias-wipro-buys-cloud-services-consultancy-appirio-for-500m/|archive-date=10 January 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fortune.com/2016/10/20/wipro-buys-appirio/|title=Why IT Services Giant Wipro Is Snapping Up Appirio for $500 Million.|last=FORTUNE|website=Fortune|access-date=2016-12-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161226220020/http://fortune.com/2016/10/20/wipro-buys-appirio/|archive-date=26 December 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2017, the company expanded its operations in London.<ref>{{Citation \n| publication-date = December 6, 2017\n| title    =Wipro to expand operations in London, to set up 3rd office \n| newspaper  =[[The Economic Times]] \n| url =https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/ites/wipro-to-expand-operations-in-london-to-set-up-3rd-office/articleshow/61951957.cms\n| accessdate  =\n}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Wipro Limited won a five-year IT infrastructure and applications managed services engagement with Grameenphone (GP), a major telecom operator in Bangladesh and announced it would set up a new delivery centre there.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wipro.com/newsroom/press-releases/2017/wipro-wins-managed-services-engagement-with-grameenphone/|title=Wipro Wins Managed Services Engagement with Grameenphone|website=www.wipro.com|accessdate=28 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, the company began building software to help with the [[General Data Protection Regulation]] (GDPR) in Europe.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/ites/indian-it-like-wipro-cognizant-set-to-cash-in-on-eus-privacy-regime/articleshow/64088184.cms|title=Indian IT like Wipro, Cognizant set to cash in on EU's privacy regime|last=Christopher|first=Nilesh|date=2018-05-09|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2018-05-30|last2=Pramanik|first2=Ayan}}</ref> In March 2018, Wipro said it would be buying a third of Denim Group.<ref>\n{{Citation\n |last             = Mendonca\n |first            = Jochelle\n |publication-date = March 1, 2018\n |title            = Wipro to buy a third of US application security company for $8.8 million\n |newspaper        = [[The Economic Times]]\n |url              = https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/ites/wipro-to-buy-a-third-of-us-application-security-company-for-8-8-million/articleshow/63126667.cms\n |archive-url      = https://web.archive.org/web/20180418121014/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/ites/wipro-to-buy-a-third-of-us-application-security-company-for-8-8-million/articleshow/63126667.cms\n |archive-date     = 18 April 2018\n |url-status         = live\n}}\n</ref> In April 2018, the company sold its stake in the airport IT services company JV.<ref>{{Citation \n| publication-date = April 6, 2018\n| title    =Wipro sells 63% stake in airport IT services JV \n| newspaper  =[[The Economic Times]] \n| url =https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/ites/wipro-sells-63-stake-in-airport-it-services-jv/articleshow/63647810.cms\n| accessdate  =\n}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2018, Wipro paid US$75m to National Grid US as a settlement for a botched SAP implementation that a 2014 audit estimated could cost the company US$1 billion. Wipro had been hired as systems integrator in 2010, but errors in the rollout, intended to replace an Oracle system, caused serious losses and reputational damage.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2018/08/06/botched_sap_implementation_national_grid_wipro_settlement_75m/|title=Wipro hands $75m to National Grid US after botched SAP upgrade|last=Hill|first=Rebecca|date=6 August 2018|work=[[The Register]]|access-date=6 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180907032415/https://www.theregister.co.uk/2018/08/06/botched_sap_implementation_national_grid_wipro_settlement_75m/|archive-date=7 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nTo compete with [[Hindustan Unilever]] and [[Procter & Gamble]], in May 2018 Wipro Consumer Care and Lighting announced it would increase Indian distribution of its acquired personal care brands Enchanteur and [[Yardley of London|Yardley]]. Other recent acquisitions included Unza Holdings, LD Waxson, and [[Zhongshan]].<ref name=\"A\">\n{{Citation\n |last             = Bhushan\n |first            = Ratna\n |publication-date = May 3, 2018\n |title            = Wipro consumer to push global brands in India\n |newspaper        = [[The Economic Times]]\n |url              = https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/ites/wipro-consumer-to-push-global-brands-in-india/articleshow/64009091.cms\n |access-date      = 1 June 2018\n |archive-url      = https://web.archive.org/web/20180503120050/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/ites/wipro-consumer-to-push-global-brands-in-india/articleshow/64009091.cms\n |archive-date     = 3 May 2018\n |url-status         = live\n}}\n</ref> On May 3, 2018, it was announced that Wipro was opening manufacturing locations in [[Andhra Pradesh]] and [[Guangzhou]].<ref>{{Citation \n| publication-date = May 3, 2018\n| title    =BRIEF-Wipro Consumer Care & Lighting Plans To Add Manufacturing Locations In Andhra Pradesh, Guangzhou\n| newspaper  =[[Reuters]] \n| url =https://www.reuters.com/article/brief-wipro-consumer-care-lighting-plans/brief-wipro-consumer-care-lighting-plans-to-add-manufacturing-locations-in-andhra-pradesh-guangzhou-idUSFWN1SA05J\n| accessdate  =\n}}</ref> On May 4, 2018, it was reported that Wipro's stock value had been decreasing.<ref name=\"B\">{{Citation \n| publication-date = May 4, 2018\n| title    =Wipro hits 10-month low; chart signals further downside\n| newspaper  =[[The Hindu Business Line]] and [[Reuters]]\n| url =https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/markets/stock-markets/wipro-hits-10-month-low-chart-signals-further-downside/article23769190.ece \n}}</ref> The day earlier, it was reported that [[HCL Technologies|HCL]] would likely unseat Wipro that quarter as the third largest Indian IT company, after TCS and [[Infosys]].<ref name=\"D\">\n{{Citation\n |last             = Phadnis\n |first            = Shilpa\n |publication-date = May 3, 2018\n |title            = HCL likely to unseat Wipro as No. 3 IT player this quarter\n |newspaper        = [[The Times of India]]\n |url              = https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/hcl-likely-to-unseat-wipro-as-no-3-it-player-this-quarter/articleshow/64010084.cms\n |access-date      = 1 June 2018\n |archive-url      = https://web.archive.org/web/20180504033426/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/business/india-business/hcl-likely-to-unseat-wipro-as-no-3-it-player-this-quarter/articleshow/64010084.cms\n |archive-date     = 4 May 2018\n |url-status         = live\n}}\n</ref>\n\n===2019-2020===\nIn 2019, Wipro Consumer Care and the Ang-Hortaleza Corporation signed a share purchase agreement for the sale of 100% of the latter's stake in the personal care business of [[Splash Corporation]], the companies announced on Monday, April 29.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com//business/229270-indian-company-wipro-acquires-splash-corporation|title=Indian company Wipro acquires beauty products maker Splash|first=Ralf|last=Rivas|website=Rappler|accessdate=22 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190429103955/https://www.rappler.com/business/229270-indian-company-wipro-acquires-splash-corporation|archive-date=29 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Wipro partnered with [[Moogsoft]], an AIOps company.<ref>{{Cite web|date=12 June 2019|accessdate=4 January 2020|publisher=[[Terra.com|Terra (company)]]|title=Wipro realiza parceria com a Moogsoft para oferecer solu\u00e7\u00f5es de AIOps de \u00faltima gera\u00e7\u00e3o|url=https://www.terra.com.br/noticias/dino/wipro-realiza-parceria-com-a-moogsoft-para-oferecer-solucoes-de-aiops-de-ultima-geracao,0220cf98235465023a1a8c7c0bb948c13m9v2hmc.html}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2020, Wipro acquired Rational Interaction, a Seattle-based digital customer experience consultancy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.consulting.us/news/3805/wipro-digital-acquires-cx-consulting-firm-rational-interaction|title=Wipro Digital acquires CX consulting firm Rational Interaction|date=2020-02-24|website=www.consulting.us|language=en|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\n==Subsidiaries==\n{{See also|Wipro Enterprises#Subsidiaries}}\n\n===Western India Products Limited===\nWipro Limited is a provider of IT services, including Systems Integration, Consulting, Information Systems outsourcing, IT-enabled services, and R&D services.<ref name=\"Company Profile for Wipro\" />\n\nWipro entered into the technology business in 1981 and has over 160,000 employees and clients across 110 countries.<ref name=\"Wipro launches iPhone app\" /> IT revenues were at $7.1 billion for the year ended 31 March 2015, with a repeat business ratio of over 95%.<ref name=\"Results for the quarter and year ended March 31, 2013 under IFRS\" /><ref name=\"Industry, Materials and Utilities\" />\n\n===Wipro GE Medical Systems===\nWipro GE Medical Systems Limited is Wipro's joint venture with GE Healthcare South Asia. It is engaged in the research and development of healthcare products. This partnership, which began in 1990,<ref name=\"Wipro GE to consolidate healthcare biz\"/> today includes gadgets and equipment for diagnostics, healthcare IT and services to help healthcare professionals combat cancer, heart disease, and other ailments. There is complete adherence to [[Six Sigma]] quality standards in all products.<ref name=\"About Wipro GE Healthcare\"/><ref name=\"Six Sigma has worked wonders for Wipro GE\"/><ref name=\"Six Sigma has worked wonders for Wipro GE1\"/>\n\n==Sustainability==\nWipro was ranked 1st in the 2010 Asian Sustainability Rating (ASR) of Indian companies<ref name=\"Wipro continues to lead in sustainability disclosures\"/> and is a member of the [[NASDAQ]] Global Sustainability Index<ref name=\"Nasdaq-100 includes Wipro in Global Sustainability Index\"/> as well as the [[Dow Jones Sustainability Index]].<ref name=\"Wipro Named Among World's Most Ethical Companies\"/>\n\nIn November 2012 ''Guide to Greener Electronics'', [[Greenpeace]] ranked Wipro first with a score of 7.1/10.<ref name=\"greenpeace\"/>\n\n==Listing and shareholding==\n{{contradict|section|date=July 2017}}\n'''Listing''': Wipro's Initial Public Offering was in the year 1946. Wipro's equity shares are listed on [[Bombay Stock Exchange]] where it is a constituent of the [[BSE SENSEX]] index,<ref name=\"Scripwise Weightages in S&P BSE SENSEX\"/> and the [[National Stock Exchange of India]] where it is a constituent of the [[S&P CNX Nifty]].<ref name=\"Download List of CNX Nifty stocks (.csv)\"/> The [[American depositary receipt|American Depositary Shares]] of the company are listed at the [[NYSE]] since October 2000.<ref name=\"SECForm20F\"/>\n\n'''Shareholding''': The table provides the share holding pattern as of 30-Sep-2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wipro.com/content/dam/nexus/en/investor/shareholding-pattern/2018/shareholding-pattern-q2-2018-19.pdf|title=Wipro Sep 2018 Sharholding pattern}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Shareholders (as on 30-Sep-2018)!! Shareholding\n|-\n| [[Corporate promoter|Promoter]] group led by Azim Premji||74.03%\n|-\n| Public||25.21%\n|-\n| Share held by Employes Trust||0.48%\n|-\n| Non Promoter Non Public Shares||0.48%\n|}\n\n==Employees==\n[[Abidali Neemuchwala]] was appointed as Wipro's CEO after [[T. K. Kurien]] stepped down in early 2016. Neemuchwala, who had been group president and CEO from April 2015, was appointed CEO with effect from 1 February 2016.<ref>\n{{Cite news\n| url = http://www.thehindu.com/business/Industry/wipro-names-abid-ali-neemuchwala-as-ceo/article8064911.ece\n| title = Wipro names Abid Ali Neemuchwala as CEO\n| date = 2016-01-04\n| newspaper = The Hindu\n| language = en-IN\n| issn = 0971-751X\n| access-date = 2016-05-22\n| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20161107100117/http://www.thehindu.com/business/Industry/wipro-names-abid-ali-neemuchwala-as-ceo/article8064911.ece\n| archive-date = 7 November 2016\n| url-status=live\n}}\n</ref>\n\n==Awards and recognitions==\n* In 2018, Wipro received ATD's Best of the BEST Award.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.td.org/magazines/td-magazine/atds-2018-best-award-winners-revealed|title = ATD's 2018 BEST Award Winners Revealed| website = ATD |language=en}}</ref>\n* In March 2017, Wipro was recognized as one of the world's most ethical companies by US-based Ethisphere Institute for the sixth consecutive year.<ref>{{cite web|url =http://asianlite.com/business/wipro-voted-worlds-most-ethical-firm/|title =Wipro Voted World\u2019s Most Ethical Firm|date =|accessdate =|website =|publisher =|last =|first =|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20150315021947/http://asianlite.com/business/wipro-voted-worlds-most-ethical-firm/|archive-date =15 March 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"hindustantimes\"/><ref name=\"indiainfoline\"/><ref>{{cite web|url =http://ethisphere.com/ethisphere-announces-2017-worlds-most-ethical-companies/|title =Ethisphere Announces 2017 World's Most Ethical Companies|date =|accessdate =|website =|publisher =|last =|first =|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20170318083926/http://ethisphere.com/ethisphere-announces-2017-worlds-most-ethical-companies/|archive-date =18 March 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* In May 2016, it was ranked 755th on the [[Forbes Global 2000]] list.<ref name=\"Wipro on Forbes Global 2000\"/>\n* Wipro won Gold Award for \u2018Integrated Security Assurance Service (iSAS)\u2019 under the \u2018Vulnerability Assessment, Remediation and Management\u2019 category of the 11th Annual 2015 Info Security PG's Global Excellence Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.infosecurityproductsguide.com/world/|title =Wipro won Gold Award for \u2018Integrated Security Assurance Service (iSAS)\u2019|date =|accessdate =|website =|publisher =|last =|first =|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20180330183151/http://www.infosecurityproductsguide.com/world/|archive-date =30 March 2018|url-status=dead|df =dmy-all}}</ref>\n* Wipro won 7 awards, including Best Managed IT Services and Best System Integrator in the CIO Choice Awards 2015, India<ref>{{cite web|url =http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/wipro-wins-seven-awards-at-cio-choice-honor-and-recognition-2015-115021901062_1.html|title =Wipro won 7 awards, including Best Managed IT Services and Best System Integrator in the CIO Choice Awards 2015, India\u2019|date =|accessdate =|website =|publisher =|last =|first =|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/we